text: Térraba-Sierpe Wetland (), is a protected area in Costa Rica, managed under the Osa Conservation Area, it was created in 1994 by decree 22993-MIRENEM. It has been designated as a protected Ramsar site since 1995. == References == Category:Ramsar sites in Costa Rica Category:Nature reserves in Costa Rica Category:Protected areas established in 1994
